  "prompt": "Dating and Relationship: Is it wrong if a girl makes the first move?",
  "response": "Absolutely not! It\u2019s not wrong at all for a girl to make the first move. In fact, it can be empowering and sets a positive tone for equality in a relationship. Traditionally, societal norms have often expected men to initiate romantic interest, but these norms are evolving. \n\nMaking the first move shows confidence, initiative, and clarity about what you want, which are all attractive qualities. It can also help break the ice and reduce miscommunication, as you\u2019re directly expressing your interest. \n\nEveryone appreciates being pursued or shown interest, regardless of gender. If you\u2019re interested in someone, go ahead and make the first move\u2014it could lead to something wonderful! Just be respectful and mindful of the other person\u2019s feelings and boundaries.",
